narrative_summary: - User requested creation of a new dbt component named 'acme_dbt' pointing to the jaffle_shop repository
- Invoked **dagster-skills:dagster-expert** skill, which routed to the **dagster-skills:dagster-integrations** skill for dbt-specific integration guidance
- Read reference documentation to understand the component-based dbt integration workflow
- Created a todo list with three tasks: install dagster-dbt, identify the required dbt adapter, and scaffold the component
- Used WebFetch to examine the jaffle_shop repository's profiles.yml and determined it uses DuckDB
- Installed the `dbt-duckdb` adapter library using `uv add dbt-duckdb`
- Scaffolded the dbt component using `dg scaffold defs dagster_dbt.DbtProjectComponent acme_dbt --git-url https://github.com/dagster-io/jaffle_shop.git --project-path .`
- Verified the component configuration by reading the generated defs.yaml file
- Validated the setup by running `uv run dg check defs` (all definitions loaded successfully)
- Listed all definitions with `uv run dg list defs` to confirm 8 dbt assets and 20 asset checks were loaded from the jaffle_shop project
